article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- — John Poulakidas scored 17 points to help Yale defeat Pennsylvania 76-62 on Friday night, increasing the Bulldogs' win streak to 10 and the Quakers' losing streak to seven. Poulakidas shot 6 for 13 (2 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 3 from the free-throw line for the Bulldogs (17-6, 8-0 Ivy League). Bez Mbeng added 16 points, six assists and five rebounds. Danny Wolf pitched in with 14 points and 10 rebounds. The Quakers (9-14, 1-7) were led by Clark Slajchert with 12 points. Tyler Perkins and Sam Brown both scored 11. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
